		<hr size="1">Not if they are doing something else, and unfortunately for you, most Druids have lives of their own and can't stand around teleporting every single charity case that wants them to drop what they are doing.  Oh, did you ever stop to ask a wizard, or were Druids the only people you targeted to victimize?  There's also a little thing called "Bind Affinity" that works well for people when they travel, too.  I play a Ranger, Bard and Monk, and none of them leave a new city without getting a bind.  I know sometimes you get killed on your way to a bind point, and that can't be helped, but you have to realise that it ISN'T other player's responsibility to take care of you.  They didn't buy this game to be free airlines for everyone else.  I'm so f**king tired of people whining about Druids or Wizards charging for a teleports!  A lot of them are really nice about taking people on corpse retrievals for free if you just wait and do an /ooc.  I've never had to wait for very long for a port on a corpse retrieval when I say I need one in /ooc...but then again, I don't send tells to strangers, bugging the living shit out of them because I've mistook them for my mommy.</P><P>Sorry for the rant, but people like this guy above are exactly the kind of players that are loot whores in groups, beg strangers to give them their equipment, train onto lower level players, and generally make a career out of being annoying.  Druids don't owe anybody their time and mana.  They aren't assholes just for saying no, or for asking for a donation for their time.  The guy probably quoted such an outrageous price because he knew it was an outrageous price and he only quoted it to get you to leave him alone.  You'd be amazed at how few steps Druids can take into any populated area before they're assulted on all sides by strangers who practically ORDER them to buff, sow and port them.  Sending people tells isn't going to do anything except make them mad.  Learn some manners before you expect other players to halt THEIR game for you, and at least do an /ooc.  According to a Wizzie friend of mine, ignoring people who send you tells does no good, either.  Doesn't matter if they're in a group or not, when some freeloader sends them a tell asking for something, Teleporting classes are branded with the mark of Cain no matter how they go about turning them down.  Learn how to take no for an answer and just keep looking.  Don't get pissed if someone wants you to pay them a lot of cash for a service, because that is what they feel their time is worth.  If you don't want to pay it, wait around, or use those little things at the bottom of your legs...what are they called?  Oh, yeah...FEET!</P><P>"Run for it!  My magic doesn't work!?"<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
	</font>
