		<hr size="1">I do have to say there are some porters (not druid specific) that are just plain greedy. Not talking about charity, but overcharging. I will pay whatever the port is worth me to and what I can afford, and if the porter is particularly patient or helpful, I'll pay more. If the porter has time to wait, I twitch there mana back unless I'm on some urgent mission. But being refused a port to someplace because someone thinks I should be able to afford more is bogus. </P><P>Example 1:</P><P>In EC, just spent most of my pp on tinkering, had about 25pp to my name at level 38. I shout "I need a port to NK please, donating". Now NK is not far from EC, but im KOS at least part of the way no matter which way I take so porting is faster and safer and worth 10 or 20pp to me in this case. I get one tell from a druid offering to port if I payed 60pp. I told him I would pay 20 and was told "no you need to pay more because of your level". I say forget it ill walk, he said "I'll sow you for 5pp", I told him I would rather deathwalk there. </P><P>Example 2:</P><P>Sitting at druid rings in WC 2 days ago, shouted for a port to GD offering 50pp. I get a tell "100pp and I will take you". I told him I would pay 50, he said nope not enuff. I do a / greedy_bastid all a few mins later and he is in GD; he was going anyways. Fine he was 50pp poorer and took me another 15 mins to get to GD, but why? I see no sense in it.</P><P>I honestly dislike greed more than begging. And I can't stand beggars.</P><P>end rant.</P><P>I have more good experiences with porters than bad, just the few bad apples really hurt the porting community's reputation for some people. Just as the "You owe me a port cuz you can and its your job" types degrade the rep of us portees.</P><P></P><P>Eternall Slumber<BR>42nd Gnome Necromancer<BR>Tholuxe Paells<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
