		<hr size="1">I've read all the posts here and several other posts about this topic in general... It all comes down to this: don't want to walk? Play a Druid yourself. When have you EVER gone through life and not pay for something? Don't get me wrong, I buff and bind for free when I can... but those that demand it of me? I'll jack up the price like there's no tomorrow.</P><P>In fact, lemme tell you a little story...</P><P>I was in Freeport medding, when a little gnome rogue came up to me asking me for a bind. I simply explained to him that I was on my way to a group that asked for my help and that I was merely medding to get my mana up.. I couldn't help him. I wasn't rude, I wasn't mean. I told him in the nicest way possible "no". Do you think it'd just stop there? Of course not... He began to bitch and complain how we Druids have a "god like" complex and we treat others like subserviants (sp?) because spells like "Bind" and "SoW" are needed greatly... blah, blah, blah. I tried to keep my cool by just letting him know that there was a group waiting on me (and has been waiting because I had to run to the bank) and that I couldn't do it. Naturally he didn't stop there. Right about before my brain had an aneurysm, I gave the group leader a tell to let him know I was going to be a few minutes longer. Then I told the rogue that it would cost him 100pp. When he flipped his 3'3" body off the ground at the inflated price, I said "still complaining?... the price just went up to 120pp"... then he said "you can't do that!"... I got up, casted SoW on myself and said "Well... then I guess you're up $hit's creek, pal. Find another Druid to do it for you. I'm late for a group." and I left.</P><P>My point: If I say I can't, there's a good reason for it. Don't push me or try to badger me if I say no. More than likely you'll get a rude and sarcastic answer. When I created a Druid character, no where did it say under class the word: SLAVE. Karma doesn't just work in the real world, people.. it'll work in this game too. What goes around comes around. Be nice and you'll get nice. It's as simple as that.</P><P>Mysidia<BR>Two Fisted Drinking Druidess of the 17th Season.<BR>Xev Server<BR>Proud Guild Scribe for Phoenix Phyre.<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
